  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Documentation Assisstant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>United Raw Material Pte. Ltd. is a reputed enterprise actively engaged in the supply of Textile Raw materials, Petrochemicals, Chemicals, Scrap & Minerals. We trade in Polyester Filament yarn, Polyester Spun Yarn, Viscose Filament Yarn, Viscose Spun Yarn, Nylon Yarn, Cotton yarn, Poly-cotton & Poly-Viscose Blended Yarns, PET Chips - Textile & Bottle Grade, PTA, MEG, Phthalica Anhydride, Maleic Anhydride, Soda Ash, Caustic Soda, PVC Resin, and several other products.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare import and export documentation accurately to support shipping and customs processes</li><li>Coordinate with shipping lines and sales team to manage Switch Bills of Lading (B/L) efficiently</li><li>Compile and send required documents to banks for Letters of Credit (LC), Trust Receipts (TR), Documents against Payment (DP), and Documents against Acceptance (DA) transactions</li><li>Follow up with banks to ensure timely financing of export documents</li><li>Arrange courier delivery of documents to buyers to meet shipment deadlines</li><li>Issue Certificates of Origin and Insurance certificates using the online portal to comply with trade requirements</li><li>Maintain organized filing of all documentation to support audit and retrieval needs</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams and external partners to ensure smooth documentation flow and compliance</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience coordinating with banks for handling trade finance documentation will be an advantage</li><li>Minimum 1 year of experience in office documentation or related administrative roles</li></ul>",
